frameDefinitions: An Agent causes a Patient to be affected, sometimes by a particular Means or by use of an Instrument.
A Cognizer has a Judgment of an Evaluee, expressing how high or low their regard for the Evaluee is.
An Agent expends effort towards achieving a Goal.
There exist a number of different possible Situations that may happen in the future.
This is an abstract frame for acts performed by sentient beings.
An Agent or a Cause mentally or physically expends energy rendering an Input, whether implicit or explicit, into a Output.
frameExamples: A professional dishwasher doesn't <t>do</t> dishes with a rag anymore!
What do you <t>think</t> of him as a linguist?
In addition, our organization will <t>work</t> on improving accountability in every department.
You have but two <t><fex name='Situation'>choices</fex></t> for your daughter .
Erosion is the <t>work</t> of wind and water on rock.
listRoleDefinitions: This role identifies the act that the <fen>Agent</fen> performs intentionally.
The conscious entity, generally a person, that performs the intentional act that affects the <fen>Patient</fen>.
Patient is the entity acted on and that may, but need not, undergo a change.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> intentionally affects the <fen>Patient</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Agent</fen> performs the intentional act.
The <fen>Cognizer</fen> is the one that makes a <fen>Judgment</fen>. This role is typically expressed as the External Argument (or in a <ment>by</ment>-PP in passives).
<fen>Evaluee</fen> is the person or thing that a judgment is made with respect to. With verbs this role is typically expressed as Object:
A description (from the point of view of the <fen>Cognizer</fen>) of the position of the <fen>Evaluee</fen> on a scale of approval.
The <fen>Agent</fen> puts effort into reaching <fen>Goal</fen>.
The <fen>Goal</fen> is what the <fen>Agent</fen> expends effort to achieve.
An entity that is centrally involved in the <fen>Goal</fen> that the <fen>Agent</fen> is attempting to acheive.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the effort occurs.
The place where the work is done.
Something that may happen in the future, or at least whose factual status is unresolved. This is often tagged in a second role layer and generally contains the target.

An individual involved in the <fen>Event</fen>.

'<fex name='Agent'>You</fex> have a <t>choice</t>.'
An entity intimately involved in the <fen>Event</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Act</fen> that the <fen>Agent</fen> performs intentionally.
The <fen>Agent</fen> performs the intentional act.
This role identifies the time when the Agent acts intentionally.
This role identifies the place where the intentional act occurs.
A sentient entity whose physical and mental faculties are directly expended on the <fen>Input</fen> to create the <fen>Output</fen>.
A non-sentient entity whose physical faculties are directly expended on the <fen>Input</fen> to create the <fen>Output</fen>.
The mental or physical faculties onto which the <fen>Agent</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen> expends energy.
The end product, either a concept or physical object onto which the <fen>Agent</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen> has exerted its mental or physical faculties from the rudimentary state of <fen>Input</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Output</fen> was committed into reality.
The place where the <fen>Output</fen> was birthed.
listRoleExamples: A professional dishwasher does <fex>dishes</fex> one at a time.
<fex>The boss</fex> appreciates you for your diligence.
I hold him in the <fex>highest</fex> esteem.
You have one choice to make <fex>for him</fex>.
